Sir Louis - Amable Jetté , (; 15 January 1836 – 5 May 1920 ) was a Canadian lawyer , politician , judge , professor , and the eighth Lieutenant Governor of Quebec .
He was born in L'Assomption , Lower Canada ( now Quebec ) in 1836 .
In 1872 , he was elected to the House of Commons of Canada representing the riding of Montreal East .
A Liberal , he was re - elected in 1874 .
Jetté was chief justice of the Court of King ’s Bench .
From 1898 to 1908 he was the lieutenant governor of Quebec .
He was knighted as a Knight Commander of the Order of St Michael and St George ( KCMG ) during the visit to Quebec of TRH the Duke and Duchess of Cornwall and York ( later King George V and Queen Mary ) in October 1901 .
